The Finance Ministry has asked Japanesecommercial banks to moderate their dollar sales, bank dealerssaid.    They said the Ministry had telephoned city and long-termbanks earlier this week to make the request.    One dealer said this was the first time the Ministry hadmade such a request to commercial banks.    Finance Ministry officials were unavailable for immediatecomment. Dealers said the Ministry has already askedinstitutional investors to reduce their sales of the dollar.   REUTER&#3;